Chief Delphi wizards - Looking for help as I am not super familiar with troubleshooting java code.

Behavior - Code builds and deploys just fine. All green lights on the Driver Station. However, when we enable TeleOP, the robot disables and throws the error “java.lang.NullPointerException” at us.

From I’ve read in other CD threads, this means we are not calling up motors in a place that we are supposed to… or something.

Here is our code - https://github.com/qbranch4327/RapidReact-Competition-Bot.git

I am VERY new to command based programming so please treat me like you would a small chimpanzee or medium sized llama.

Any help is appreciated. Thanks!
